cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a new region-of-interest (RoI) feature extraction strategy for instance segmentation, which is a computer vision task (cs.CV). The proposed method involves refining the bounding box and mask predicted by Mask R-CNN, which is a popular deep learning model for object detection and segmentation, indicating the paper may also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The proposed method also aims to address the issue of segmenting huddled instances, which is a problem in robotics and automation (cs.RO). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on the COCO dataset, which is a widely used benchmark in multimedia (cs.MM).
